<document title="Breakpoint menu" output="studio">
	<meta_data/>
	<paragraph>
		<heading>
			<size>1</size>Conditional breakpoints
		</heading>
		<paragraph>A condition breakpoint is a breakpoint in which debugger will stop if a certain condition is met. To set a conditional breakpoint use the 
			<link>
				<url>10_breakpoint_menu.xml</url>
				<label>breakpoint menu</label>
			</link> and choose `Set conditional breakpoint':
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph>
			<image>
				<url>../../../../../images/eiffelstudio/debugger/breakpoint_context_menu.png</url>
			</image>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph>Once done a dialog pops up where you can enter a condition:</paragraph>
		<paragraph>
			<image>
				<url>../../../../../images/eiffelstudio/dialogs_and_wizards/enter_condition.png</url>
			</image>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph>The condition is a Boolean expression that follows the same rule as the expression you can enter in the 
			<link>
				<url>../50_expression_evaluation/index.xml</url>
				<label>expression evaluation tool</label>
			</link>.
			<line_break></line_break>
		</paragraph>
